\int_x^1\frac{dt}{1+t^2}=\int_1^{1/x}\frac{dt}{1+t^2},\;x>0.
u
t=x
u=1/x
 \begin{align} u & = \frac 1 t \\[8pt] du & = \frac{-dt}{t^2} \\[8pt] -t^2\,du & = dt \\[8pt] \frac{-du}{u^2} & = dt \end{align} 
 \int_1^x \frac{dt}{1+t^2} = \int_1^{1/x} \frac{-du/u^2}{1+(1/u)^2} = \int_1^{1/x} \frac{-du}{u^2+1}. 
t \leftarrow 1/t
\int_1^x {dt\over 1 + t^2 } = \int_{1/x}^1 {dt/t^2\over 1 + (1/t)^2} = \int_{1/x}^1 {dt\over 1 + t^2}. 
